The discharge from your nose may become thicker and yellow or green in color as a common cold runs its course. This isn't an indication of a bacterial infection.\par
When to see a doctor\par
For adults \f1\emdash  seek medical attention if you have:\par
Fever greater than 101.3 F (38.5 C)\par
Fever lasting five days or more or returning after a fever-free period\par
Shortness of breath\par
Wheezing\par
Severe sore throat, headache or sinus pain\par
